{"id": "EUVD-2024-53760", "enisaUuid": "4806a116-2326-3a43-b113-9aa9ec98b2a1", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nscsi: mpi3mr: Fix corrupt config pages PHY state is switched in sysfs\n\nThe driver, through the SAS transport, exposes a sysfs interface to\nenable/disable PHYs in a controller/expander setup.  When multiple PHYs\nare disabled and enabled in rapid succession, the persistent and current\nconfig pages related to SAS IO unit/SAS Expander pages could get\ncorrupted.\n\nUse separate memory for each config request.", "datePublished": "2025-01-11T15:30:29", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-17T15:30:55", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/869fdc6f0606060301aef648231e186c7c542f5a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/711201a8b8334a397440ac0b859df0054e174bc9", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-57804"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-57804"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "50342e4c-b267-39f2-b21a-e1b4219fd528", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32d457d5a2af9bf5ddbe28297eabf1fc93451665 <869fdc6f0606060301aef648231e186c7c542f5a"}, {"id": "5096486e-42a2-37a1-bf13-6bbde82f4048", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "600c3cd4-17c9-3ad6-8281-48db96451841", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.1"}, {"id": "68d64547-b240-378e-abc6-d496f583714f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "ecc7c85f-3ddc-3cbe-8edf-c0b433992d80", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32d457d5a2af9bf5ddbe28297eabf1fc93451665 <711201a8b8334a397440ac0b859df0054e174bc9"}, {"id": "fc829883-6c5c-36e8-971e-025871062b67", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.8"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "c78b2e95-747d-3ce7-85ec-dfc705d54a19", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}